cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper presents a method for facial landmark detection using deep neural networks and model-based fitting algorithms. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as the primary sub-category. The use of deep neural networks for predicting model parameters also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are likely sub-categories. The evaluation of the method on different datasets for facial landmark detection and medical image segmentation suggests that multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) are also possible sub-categories.
